The paper discusses a framework for deriving and analyzing online optimization algorithms that incorporate adaptive, data-dependent regularization. This topic is closely related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the AdaGrad and Online Newton Step algorithms, which are commonly used in deep learning and optimization, respectively, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
